                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote"/>
                           <locus target="#1v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘደብተራ፡ <add place="overstrike">አርከ፡ ድንግል፡ </add> መነኮስ፡ ዘአጥረዮ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ ለመድኃኒተ፡ ወነፍሱ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡
                    ወፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">This book is of the <foreign>dabtarā</foreign> monk <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11706ArkaDengel">ʾArka Dǝngǝl</persName>, the monk, which he acquired with his own money
                    so that it might become salvation for his soul. Anyone who has stole it or erase its (text) will be excommunicated through the authority of Peter and Paul.</q>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote"> </desc>
                           <locus target="#49v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ አብ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">This book is of our
                             father <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11707WaldaAb">Walda ʾAb.</persName>
                           </q>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc type="ProtectivePrayer"/>
                           <locus from="72v" to="73r"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡ ወአመ፡ ይመጽእ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ውስተ፡ ዓለም፡ ከመ፡ ይኅድር፡ ውስተ፡ ማኅፀና፡ ለድንግል፡
                    ማርያም፡ አርዌ፡ ምድር፡ ተካይደ፡ ወዲያብሎስ፡ ተሰደ፡ ይልሳሕ፡ ኅምዙ፡ ለአርዌ፡ ምድር፡ ወይትቀጥቀጥ፡ መሰረታተ፡ ኅምዝ፡ ወይቤሎ፡
                    ለሙሴ፡ <cit>
                      <q xml:lang="gez">ግበር፡ ለከ፡ አርዌ፡ ምድር፡ ዘብረት፡ ኵሉ፡ ዘነሰኮ፡ ይርአይ፡ ኪያሁ፡ ወይሕየው፡ </q>
                      <ref cRef="betmas:LIT2075Number.21.8"> </ref>
                        </cit> ኪዮስ፡ ኪዮሳዊ፡ አቅላሚድ፡ መልአኩ፡ ለአርዌ፡ ምድር፡ ወአግዓዚ፡ በኃይለ፡ ክርስቶስ፡
                    ወአኅዝኩ፡ ቀረፀ፡ ወአፃፃ፡ ወአፀውኩ፡ ፈውሳ፡ ፈውሰ፡ ኩን፡ ፈውስ፡ ተመን፡ ኩን፡ ፈውስ፡ ፈውሰ፡ አፍዖት፡ በጸሎተ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ወማርቆስ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ወዮሐንስ፡ አርባዕተ፡ ወንጌላውያን፡ ኅደግ፡
                    ይቤለከ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አንተ፡ መዝገበ፡ ሕየው፡ አርጣን፡ አርዮን፡ እቶንክዮን፡ ድምናኤል፡ ካዙዛኤል፡ ካፍ፡ ካፍ፡ ፯፡ ፯፡ ጊዜ፡ በል፡ ኅምዙ፡ ለከይሲ፡ ኢይዕርግ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ ወኢይረድ፡
                    ታሕቴሁ፡ ለገበረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ <del rend="erasure" extent="unknown"/>
                              <add place="unspecified"/>h1፡ በዙኃ፡ ጊዜ፡ ወዘንተ፡ ማየ፡ ስተይ፡ ወተጠመቅ፡ ቦቱ፡ በዙኃ፡ ጊዜ፡ እስከ፡ ትትፌውስ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit, one God.
                             And when Our Lord came into the world in order to
                             dwell in the womb of the Virgin Mary, the
            snake of the earth was crushed and Devil was banned and the gift of
            the snake of the earth became weak, and the foundation
            of the (strength of the) gift was destroyed.
            And it said to Moses, "Make an
            iron snake of earth <ref cRef="betmas:LIT2075Number.21.8">Numbers 21:8</ref>,
            anyone whom (a snake) would bite, should
            look at it, and he will recover". Kiyos, kiyosawi, ʾaqlāmid <gap reason="omitted"/> </q>
                           <note>Spell against snake bites</note>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc type="Unclear"> </desc>
                           <locus target="#73v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ንስር፡ ወዘሐቅለ፡ ገዳም፡ አንበሳ፡ በቅድሜከ፡ ይክበር፡ ኢያሱ፡ ለደብረ፡ ሊባኖስ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Takla Haymānot, eagle, and the lion of the field of the desert,
                             ʾIyāsu of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2297DabraL">Dabra Libānos</placeName>
                             may be honoured in front of you!</q>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc type="Poem"> </desc>
                           <locus target="#138v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">መኑ፡ ከማከ፡ ዘታነሀሲ፡ አበሳሆሙ፡ ለሕዝብከ፡ መኑ፡ ከማከ፡ ጽልመተ፡
                              በርህ፡ ዘአስተአጸቡ፡ ታቀልል፡ መኑ፡ ከማከ፡ እስመ፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Who are like you who forgive the
                              sins of your people; who are like you, who drove out the darkness;
                  who made light what they made heavy; who are like you, since</q>
                           <note>Incomplete, only the beginning.</note>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <desc type="Unclear"> </desc>
                           <locus target="#157r"/>
                           <note>Several prayers  including <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2168PaterN">Our Father</ref>,
                           written in different hands.</note>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <desc type="Unclear"> </desc>
                           <locus target="#157r"/>
                           <note>List of the commemoration feasts of the Apostles.</note>
                        </item>

                     </list>
